            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What Are Cookies?</h2>
                <p>
                    Cookies are small text files stored on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit a website. 
                    They help websites remember your preferences and improve your browsing experience.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Types of information stored:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Login sessions and authentication</li>
                    <li>User preferences and settings</li>
                    <li>Analytics and usage patterns</li>
                    <li>Marketing and advertising preferences</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-list"></i> Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

                <h3>1. Essential Cookies</h3>
                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Required for basic website functionality</p>
                    <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Session management</li>
                        <li>Security features</li>
                        <li>Load balancing</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Can be disabled?</strong> No - these are necessary for the site to work</p>
                </div>

                <h3>2. Functional Cookies</h3>
                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Remember your preferences and settings</p>
                    <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Language preferences</li>
                        <li>Region selection</li>
                        <li>Accessibility settings</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Can be disabled?</strong> Yes - but some features may not work properly</p>
                </div>

                <h3>3. Analytics Cookies</h3>
                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our website</p>
                    <p><strong>Services we use:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Website traffic and user behavior analysis</li>
                        <li><strong>Microsoft Clarity:</strong> Heatmaps and session recordings</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Data collected:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Pages visited</li>
                        <li>Time spent on site</li>
                        <li>Click patterns</li>
                        <li>Device and browser information</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Can be disabled?</strong> Yes - see "Managing Cookies" section</p>
                </div>

                <h3>4. Marketing Cookies</h3>
                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Track visitors across websites to display relevant ads</p>
                    <p><strong>Note:</strong> We currently do not use marketing cookies, but may in the future with your consent</p>
                    <p><strong>Can be disabled?</strong> Yes</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Cookie Duration</h2>

                <h3>Session Cookies</h3>
                <p>Temporary cookies deleted when you close your browser</p>
                <p><strong>Used for:</strong> Login sessions, shopping carts, form data</p>

                <h3>Persistent Cookies</h3>
                <p>Remain on your device for a set period or until manually deleted</p>
                <p><strong>Duration:</strong> Typically 1-24 months depending on purpose</p>
            </section>

